sequenceDiagram
    participant RS as Rule Service
    participant CS as Cloud Service
    participant OP as On-Prem Service
    participant AZ as Azure Blob Storage

    RS->>CS: Remediation request (instruction blob URL)
    Note over CS: Creates Transaction + State Machine
    Note over CS: ── State 0: Request Forwarding ──

    CS->>OP: Header: instruction series manifest (small-msg RMQ)
    CS->>OP: Instruction chunks (large-msg RMQ)
    Note over OP: Reconstructs work order from chunks

    Note over OP: Executes remediation on file system
    Note over OP: Modifies permissions, creates AD groups
    Note over OP: Tracks: folders, files, groups affected
    Note over CS: ── State 1: Awaiting Results ──

    OP->>CS: Header: result series manifest (small-msg RMQ)
    Note over CS: Knows exactly what is coming:<br/>which series, TotalCount per series
    OP->>CS: Result chunks — Folders series (large-msg RMQ)
    OP->>CS: Result chunks — Files series (large-msg RMQ)
    OP->>CS: Result chunks — Groups series (large-msg RMQ)

    loop For each chunk received
        CS->>AZ: Stream chunk → upload as blob
        AZ-->>CS: Blob URI
        Note over CS: URI stored in Table Storage<br/>key: TransactionId + SeriesType + Ordinal
    end

    Note over CS: All series complete (all ordinals accounted for)
    Note over CS: ── State 2: Sending Completion ──

    Note over CS: Result Assembler collects ordered<br/>URI lists per series from Table Storage
    CS->>RS: Notification: ordered blob URIs per series<br/>(Folders list, Files list, Groups list)
    Note over RS: Downloads chunks in order,<br/>reassembles full result files
